{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, state coverage feedback is employed to work with branch coverage to guide the fuzzing campaign.",
    "However, identifying states presents a significant challenge.",
    "A series of works [7], [36], [32], [38] proposes various state representation schemes.",
    "AFLNET [36] utilizes the response code as states, constructs a state machine during the fuzzing campaign, and employs it as state-coverage guidance.",
    "STATEAFL [32], SGFUZZ [7], and NSFUZZ [38] propose distinct state representation schemes based on program variables."
  ]
}